# üìê Rules for Generating High-Accuracy Wireframe Descriptions

> Use this as a system prompt or design instruction for a language model to generate reliable, professional wireframe documentation.

---

## 1. üéØ Define the Core Context

Start with a clear summary:
- **What is it?** (e.g., "SaaS Dashboard", "Mobile Shopping App")
- **Which screen?** (e.g., "Dashboard Overview", "User Registration Form")
- **Who is it for?** (Target user, e.g., "Project Managers", "Freelancers")
- **Goal of the screen?** (e.g., "Display KPIs", "Enable easy sign-up")

---

## 2. üß± Enumerate All Essential Elements

List **all UI components**, with precision:
- Header (e.g., Logo left, Search center, User Avatar right)
- Sidebar Navigation (items: Dashboard, Reports, Settings)
- Cards (e.g., Metrics, Quick Actions)
- Forms (e.g., Name input, Email input, Submit button)
- Charts (e.g., Line chart of weekly activity)
- Buttons (label each button clearly)
- Tables (include column names)
- Any other elements (filters, tags, dropdowns, tabs, modals, etc.)

---

## 3. üìê Describe Layout & Hierarchy

Specify:
- **Overall layout:** (e.g., "Header + Sidebar + 2x2 grid layout")
- **Visual priority:** (e.g., "Key Metrics are top-left and prominent")
- **Positioning:** (e.g., "Search bar to the right of logo", "Cards below header")

---

## 4. üì± Mandate Responsive Design

Ensure layout adapts across devices:
- **Desktop:** Full layout (e.g., sidebar always visible)
- **Tablet:** Sidebar may collapse to icons; grid reduces to 2 columns
- **Mobile:** Sidebar hidden in hamburger menu; cards stack vertically; font size and spacing adjusted

---

## 5. üé® Visual Style & Color Palette (Optional)

Include aesthetic guidance:
- **Style keywords:** (e.g., "Clean", "Futuristic", "Minimal", "Professional")
- **Color palette suggestion:**
  - 3‚Äì5 unique hex codes
  - Label usage: (e.g., Primary Button, Background, Accent, Text)
  - Optional theme name: (e.g., "Quantum Clarity", "Neon Blueprint")

---

## 6. üìÑ Format the Output

Always organize the wireframe text in the following structure:
1. **Header**
2. **Sidebar Navigation**
3. **Main Content Area**
4. **Footer (if applicable)**
5. **Layout & Visual Hierarchy**
6. **Responsiveness**
7. **Visual Style & Color Palette (Optional)**

Use bold section headings and bullet points for clarity.

